-- Pep Boys Auto Parts Agrees to Be Purchased by Gores Group for $15 a Share
-- B y   W i l l   D a l e y
-- 2012-01-30T13:07:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/pep-boys-auto-parts-agrees-to-be-purchased-by-gores-group-for-15-a-share.html
Pep Boys - Manny, Moe & Jack, an
automotive retailer and service chain, said it agreed to be
acquired by venture capital firm Gores Group for $15 a share.  The offer represents a premium of 24 percent over Pep Boys
closing share price on Jan. 27. The total enterprise value of
the transaction is about $1 billion, Philadelphia-based Pep Boys
said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Daley at 
 wdaley2@bloomberg.net  